properties.opoint-field.notes: This stand of at least a dozen trees is along Tilley Rd in Millerslyvania State Park. While the road basically bisect the State Park, this group of trees is a bit exposed given the creeks culvert it sits next to. There is quite a bit of standing water around the stand at the moment. I suspect it drys up middle to late summer. At least 8 trees were completely dead. Another 2 or 3 had thinning foliage throughout. There were also 3 that had been cut down at some point which you can see in the photos. Might have been cut due to their proximity to the power lines.
